{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c74e06b3-7b48-4911-9bc3-c99924f76e93","content":"`WindowSoftInputModeAdjust.Resize` was removed because Android deprecated `SOFT_INPUT_ADJUST_RESIZE` itself. Here's what to do for .NET 10:\n\n### Android\n\nSet the soft input mode directly in `Platforms/Android/MainActivity.cs`:\n\n```csharp\n[Activity(\n    Theme = \"@style/Maui.SplashTheme\",\n    MainLauncher = true,\n    WindowSoftInputMode = SoftInput.AdjustResize)]  // ← add this\npublic class MainActivity : MauiAppCompatActivity { }\n```\n\n> **Note:** MAUI's built-in `KeyboardAutoManagerScroll` scrolls the *focused control* into view but doesn't **resize the layout**, so a bottom-pinned input bar won't move up with it alone. The `AdjustResize` attribute does the resize. If `KeyboardAutoManagerScroll` fights with your layout, disable it per-page:\n\n```csharp\n#if ANDROID\nKeyboardAutoManagerScroll.Disconnect();\n#endif\n```\n\n### iOS\n\niOS doesn't resize automatically. Listen for keyboard insets and add bottom padding:\n\n```csharp\n// In your chat page or a behavior\n#if IOS\nUIKeyboard.Notifications.ObserveWillShow((sender, args) =>\n{\n    var kbHeight = args.FrameEnd.Height;\n    chatPage.Padding = new Thickness(0, 0, 0, kbHeight);\n});\nUIKeyboard.Notifications.ObserveWillHide((sender, args) =>\n{\n    chatPage.Padding = new Thickness(0);\n});\n#endif\n```\n\n### Typical chat layout (cross-platform)\n\n```xml\n<Grid RowDefinitions=\"*,Auto\">\n    <CollectionView Grid.Row=\"0\" ItemsSource=\"{Binding Messages}\" />\n    <HorizontalStackLayout Grid.Row=\"1\" Padding=\"8\">\n        <Entry Placeholder=\"Type a message...\" HorizontalOptions=\"FillAndExpand\" />\n        <Button Text=\"Send\" Command=\"{Binding SendCommand}\" />\n    </HorizontalStackLayout>\n</Grid>\n```\n\nWith `AdjustResize` on Android and the keyboard observer on iOS, the `Grid` shrinks and the `Auto`-sized bottom row stays pinned above the keyboard.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"07f0500b-2b97-4e5e-8db9-58770ead86c6","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a .NET MAUI issue where the keyboard covers the text input at the bottom of the screen. They mention that `WindowSoftInputModeAdjust.Resize` doesn't work in .NET 10 (it was deprecated/removed). This is a known issue in .NET MAUI.\n\nLet me provide the answer based on my knowledge:\n\nIn .NET 9+, `WindowSoftInputModeAdjust.Resize` was deprecated because Android itself deprecated the `SOFT_INPUT_ADJUST_RESIZE` mode. The recommended approach in .NET MAUI for .NET 10 is to use the new `KeyboardAutoManagerScroll` behavior or handle it with `Edge-to-Edge` / `WindowInsets` approach.\n\n\nSo the key issue is that Android 11+ deprecated the resize mode, and .NET MAUI followed suit. The built-in `KeyboardAutoManagerScroll` behavior should handle keyboard adjustments automatically in newer versions, though there may be edge cases where manual configuration is needed.\n\nFor a chat screen specifically, I should focus on the practical approaches: either relying on the default keyboard manager, using Android's inset-based padding adjustments, or falling back to pan mode if resize isn't available. Setting up platform-specific code in Android's MainActivity to configure the soft input mode, while leveraging MAUI's built-in keyboard management for the layout adjustments needed in a chat interface. I'll provide the practical solution for .NET 10 since this is a straightforward knowledge question.","outputTokens":1713,"requestId":"0455:3BF41F:141B540:167774E:6A027CCA"},"id":"c3b3cb6e-e201-49bc-a48c-1e39ab1f5e22","timestamp":"2026-05-12T01:05:51.249Z","parentId":"65693f09-0eb4-481a-b70a-1a6d5aa2f15f"}
